data.description: THIS SELLER SAY LET’S GO!  Price adjustment that will knock your socks off. At our current price we are BELOW comparables.  Almost 3,000  sqft of living space. In-ground pool. Over 1/2 half acre fully fenced. GIANT rv or boat storage, and just busting at the seams with history and charm! Here is your chance at a once in a lifetime home. Even though it’s 100 years old this home still has so many more years left to give. Built by the local county tax collector, Sid Graham, back in 1911. The Graham Manor, started out as a 5-bedroom home with only 1 bathroom. What is now the laundry room was added on in the 1940’s to house WWII pilots who were training at the local old airfield in Bushnell. The Clayton family bought it in the late 1960’s, then sold it to the Sullivan family in the 1990’s. That’s when this home started to get its second chance. What is now the breakfast nook and the family room was part of an open porch that was enclosed. They updated the home with all new plumbing, and new electric. They leveled the home and restored any foundation issues. In 2003 a new, lifetime metal roof was added. Then in 2017 our current seller purchased it. Only the fourth owner in almost a century, she’s been a loving steward. The original hardwood floors have been refinished. A brand-new septic and drain field installed in 2021. Also in 2021, they added a gorgeous, in-ground, salt water pool with 4 fountains and LED lights. Although you are in the middle of it all, a private, backyard oasis is right here. They created a sitting area with an antique brick fire pit, arbor, and added electric and lights to help set the scene for backyard parties or get-togethers. Also in 2021 a 35x35 RV or boat storage building was added with 50 amp electric service. The home has almost 3,000 square feet of living space and is absolutely breathtaking. Now with 3 bedrooms, and 3 bathrooms, because those 5 bedrooms were tiny, this home is ready for its next chapter. There’s no doubt this home is a place for a million new memories to be made. Flooded with natural light and an energy you can feel as you walk through the door. Formal living room, formal dining room, a kitchen that will leave you speechless, the breakfast nook, and the family room that could easily be converted to a home office or 4th bedroom. Do you wonder if there can be a 2nd floor?  Oh definitely. Come see and we will share some ideas. Sitting on well over one-half acre, fully fenced, the seller also added an electric gate in 2021. In the heart of the great town of Bushnell, across the street from the courthouse and down the road from the central business district. Watch the Bushnell Fall Festival fireworks from your front porch. This home could potentially be rezoned to professional or light commercial. Potential sewer connection available with bore under Noble Ave. Adjacent use is an established law firm on one side and another historic classic home on the other side. Original windows. 4 original fireplaces, that have all been plumbed for gas. Original baseboards and so much more. As they say, if these walls could talk, oh the stories they could tell. Showings are by appointment only. Verified proof of funds or approval letter needed to schedule a showing. Available, with appointment, seven days a week. We would love to show you this home. The whole package is truly epic! Come see for yourself.
